---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead 
			title="The Team Health Playbook — The Operating Leader" 
			description="Diagnose, fix, and maintain healthy teams without expensive tools. 40+ diagnostic questions, 3 action playbooks, and a weekly pulse framework from 20 years of scaling teams." 
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="playbook-page">
			<!-- Hero -->
			<section class="hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">A practical guide for founders & product leaders</p>
				<h1>The Team Health<br/>Playbook</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">
					How to diagnose, fix, and maintain healthy teams — without expensive tools or consultants. 
					From 20 years of building teams from 4 to 700 people.
				</p>
				<a href="#buy" class="cta-button buy-btn" onclick="handleCheckout(event)">Get the Playbook — $29</a>
				<p class="cta-sub">PDF download · 50+ pages · Instant access</p>
			</section>

			<!-- Problem -->
			<section class="section">
				<h2>You can feel it, but you can't name it.</h2>
				<p>
					Meetings are quieter than they should be. Good people leave and you're surprised. 
					Everyone's busy but nothing moves. Something's off — but engagement surveys won't tell you what.
				</p>
				<p>
					Most leaders know their team isn't healthy. They just don't have a framework 
					to diagnose <em>what's actually broken</em> and fix it systematically.
				</p>
				<p>This playbook gives you that framework.</p>
			</section>

			<!-- What's Inside -->
			<section class="section">
				<h2>What's Inside</h2>
				<div class="toc">
					<div class="toc-item">
						<span class="toc-part">Part 1</span>
						<h3>The 5 Dimensions of Team Health</h3>
						<p>Clarity, Energy, Trust, Alignment, Growth — the CETAG framework. Every team problem traces back to one of these five things.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="toc-item">
						<span class="toc-part">Part 2</span>
						<h3>Diagnostic Questions & Red Flags</h3>
						<p>40+ specific questions for 1:1s and team settings. Plus the early warning signals for each dimension — so you catch problems before they become crises.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="toc-item">
						<span class="toc-part">Part 3</span>
						<h3>Action Playbooks for the 3 Most Common Problems</h3>
						<p>The Silent Team. The Hamster Wheel. The Revolving Door. Week-by-week action plans to fix each one in 30 days.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="toc-item">
						<span class="toc-part">Part 4</span>
						<h3>The Weekly Pulse Framework</h3>
						<p>A 2-minute weekly check-in that replaces expensive engagement tools. 5 questions, trend tracking, and a Monday morning ritual that actually works.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="toc-item">
						<span class="toc-part">Part 5</span>
						<h3>Real Stories from the Trenches</h3>
						<p>What broke at Mailigen at 15 people vs. 30. How alignment collapsed during the Pipedrive PE transition. Building energy at a robotics startup.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="toc-item">
						<span class="toc-part">Part 6</span>
						<h3>The Quick Start Guide</h3>
						<p>Exactly what to do on Day 1 through Day 5. Plus a complete question bank with 40 ready-to-use diagnostic questions.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Who It's For -->
			<section class="section">
				<h2>Who This Is For</h2>
				<ul class="who-list">
					<li><strong>Founders</strong> scaling from 10 to 50 people who feel the culture shifting and don't know what lever to pull</li>
					<li><strong>Product & Engineering leaders</strong> managing teams of 5-30 who want a systematic approach to team health</li>
					<li><strong>VPs and Directors</strong> navigating organizational change — PE transitions, rapid growth, or restructuring</li>
					<li><strong>First-time managers</strong> who want to build healthy teams from the start instead of learning through painful trial and error</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<!-- Author -->
			<section class="section author-section">
				<h2>Written by Someone Who's Done It</h2>
				<div class="author">
					<div class="author-bio">
						<p>
							<strong>Janis Rozenblats</strong> has been building and leading teams for 20 years. 
							He built Mailigen from 4 people in a 12sqm office to 40 people and an acquisition. 
							As VP Product at Pipedrive, he navigated a PE transition at 700 people. 
							Now he's CPO at a robotics startup, building from scratch again.
						</p>
						<p>
							This playbook isn't theory from a consulting deck. It's the specific questions, signals, 
							and actions from two decades of getting team health right — and wrong — at every scale.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Buy -->
			<section class="section buy-section" id="buy">
				<div class="buy-box">
					<h2>Get The Team Health Playbook</h2>
					<p class="price">$29</p>
					<ul class="buy-includes">
						<li>✓ Complete playbook (50+ pages, PDF)</li>
						<li>✓ 40+ diagnostic questions — copy-paste ready</li>
						<li>✓ 3 action playbooks with week-by-week plans</li>
						<li>✓ Weekly pulse framework template</li>
						<li>✓ Instant download, keep forever</li>
					</ul>
					<a href="#buy" class="cta-button buy-btn" onclick="handleCheckout(event)">Buy Now — $29</a>
					<p class="buy-note">Secure payment via Stripe. PDF delivered instantly.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- FAQ -->
			<section class="section">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq">
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Is this just another engagement survey guide?</h3>
						<p>No. I actually argue against traditional surveys in the playbook. This is a diagnostic framework with specific questions, red flags to watch for, and action playbooks — not a data collection exercise.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>I'm a first-time manager. Is this too advanced?</h3>
						<p>It's the opposite — this is exactly what I wish I'd had as a first-time manager. The quick start guide gives you a 5-day plan to implement immediately. No experience required, just willingness to have honest conversations.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>How is this different from free leadership advice online?</h3>
						<p>Free advice tells you to "build psychological safety." This tells you which 3 questions to ask in Tuesday's 1:1, what responses to watch for, and exactly what to do when you hear them. It's the implementation manual, not the philosophy.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>What format is the playbook?</h3>
						<p>PDF. Clean, well-structured, designed to be referenced repeatedly — not read once and forgotten. You'll come back to the question bank and action playbooks constantly.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="faq-item">
						<h3>Do you offer refunds?</h3>
						<p>If you don't find it valuable, email me and I'll refund you. No questions. I've spent 20 years on this material — I'm confident you'll find it worth far more than $29.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Final CTA -->
			<section class="section final-cta">
				<p>
					Most leaders don't measure team health at all. The bar is on the floor. 
					You just need to step over it.
				</p>
				<a href="#buy" class="cta-button buy-btn" onclick="handleCheckout(event)">Get the Playbook — $29</a>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.playbook-page {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2em 1em 4em;
	}

	/* Hero */
	.hero {
		text-align: center;
		padding: 3em 0 3em;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	.eyebrow {
		text-transform: uppercase;
		font-size: 0.8em;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}
	.hero h1 {
		font-size: 3.5em;
		line-height: 1.05;
		letter-spacing: -0.04em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.subtitle {
		font-size: 1.15em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		line-height: 1.7;
		max-width: 540px;
		margin: 0 auto 2em;
	}
	.cta-button {
		display: inline-block;
		background: var(--accent);
		color: white !important;
		padding: 0.9em 2.5em;
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-weight: 600;
		font-size: 1.1em;
		text-decoration: none !important;
		transition: background 0.15s ease, transform 0.1s ease;
	}
	.cta-button:hover {
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		transform: translateY(-1px);
	}
	.cta-sub {
		font-size: 0.85em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin-top: 1em;
	}

	/* Sections */
	.section {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	.section h2 {
		font-size: 1.75em;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}
	.section p {
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	/* TOC */
	.toc {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.5em;
		margin-top: 1.5em;
	}
	.toc-item {
		padding: 1.5em;
		background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.5);
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	.toc-part {
		font-size: 0.75em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	.toc-item h3 {
		font-size: 1.15em;
		margin: 0.25em 0 0.5em;
	}
	.toc-item p {
		font-size: 0.92em;
		margin: 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	/* Who list */
	.who-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.who-list li {
		padding: 0.75em 0;
		padding-left: 1.75em;
		position: relative;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	.who-list li::before {
		content: "→";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	/* Author */
	.author-bio p {
		font-size: 1.05em;
	}

	/* Buy */
	.buy-section {
		border-bottom: none;
	}
	.buy-box {
		text-align: center;
		background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.4);
		padding: 3em 2em;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 2px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	.buy-box h2 {
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.price {
		font-size: 3em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		margin: 0 0 1em;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}
	.buy-includes {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		text-align: left;
		max-width: 380px;
		margin: 0 auto 2em;
	}
	.buy-includes li {
		padding: 0.4em 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.buy-note {
		font-size: 0.85em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin-top: 1em;
	}

	/* FAQ */
	.faq {
		margin-top: 1em;
	}
	.faq-item {
		padding: 1.25em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	.faq-item:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}
	.faq-item h3 {
		font-size: 1.05em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.faq-item p {
		font-size: 0.95em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Final CTA */
	.final-cta {
		text-align: center;
		border-bottom: none;
		padding-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.final-cta p {
		font-size: 1.2em;
		font-style: italic;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.hero h1 { font-size: 2.5em; }
		.price { font-size: 2.5em; }
		.buy-box { padding: 2em 1.5em; }
	}
	.buy-btn.loading {
		opacity: 0.6;
		pointer-events: none;
	}
</style>

<script is:inline>
async function handleCheckout(e) {
	e.preventDefault();
	const btn = e.target;
	const originalText = btn.textContent;
	btn.textContent = 'Redirecting to checkout...';
	btn.classList.add('loading');
	try {
		const res = await fetch('https://operatingleader-checkout.rozenblats.workers.dev/create-checkout', {
			method: 'POST',
			headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
		});
		const data = await res.json();
		if (data.url) {
			window.location.href = data.url;
		} else {
			alert('Checkout is being set up. Please try again shortly.');
			btn.textContent = originalText;
			btn.classList.remove('loading');
		}
	} catch (err) {
		alert('Checkout is being set up. Please try again shortly.');
		btn.textContent = originalText;
		btn.classList.remove('loading');
	}
}
</script>
